         <abstract>
            <p>
               As a converted magician, a number of magical prayers are attributed to <persName ref="PRS3247Cyprian">Cyprian of Antioch</persName>. 
               The Prayer of Cyprian is the main prayer, known in Greek, Latin, Syriac, Armenian and Georgian versions, 
               cp. <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Bausi1998Cipriano"/> 
                  <citedRange unit="page">104</citedRange>
               </bibl> and <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Simon1936ReviewBilabel"/>
               </bibl>. 
               Both Arabic and Ethiopic traditions have a long and a short recension of this prayer, see <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3578Prayer"/> and  <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3579Prayer"/>. 
            </p>
         </abstract>
